Before you start coding 

(follow the steps below to run the project)
step 1:
docker-compose -f backend/docker-compose.yml build --no-cache
docker-compose -f backend/docker-compose.yml up

step 2: cd mobile (always in mobile)

step 3: npx react-native run-android

docker down:
docker-compose -f backend/docker-compose.yml down -v

====================================================================================

error to fix:

if there is this error

"devDependencies": {
    "@react-native-community/cli": "latest",
  }


command: npm install --save-dev @react-native-community/cli@latest

(to start flask) // if flask didnt start
step 4: cd backend 
		python app.py

====================================================================================
IMPT⭐⭐⭐ NOTE from Kaibao: (Rmb to remove when deloying for production)
For instant backend refresh during development (ctrl + s)

Added: 
(volumes: - .:/app) in /backend/docker-compose.yml
(ENV FLASK_DEBUG=1) in /backend/Dockerfile

To check debugger:
/backend
CMD for backend log: docker-compose logs -f backend

To check debugger from frontend (Only works when running 1 emulator):
/mobile
CMD for front-end debug: npx react-native log-android

====================================================================================
(backend postgresql)

step 1: psql -h localhost -p 5432 -U scdf_username -d scdf_db
		password:scdf_password

-------------if have error (due to same port docker & pgadmin port 5432)--------

step 2: netstat -ano | findstr :5432


step 3: tasklist /FI "PID eq 7824"
		tasklist /FI "PID eq 21212"


step 4: Stop or disable the service/program occupying port 5432

		If either is a native PostgreSQL service, stop it to free the port:

		Open Services (press Win+R, type services.msc)

		Find PostgreSQL service(s)

		Stop and disable it temporarily


step 5: docker-compose down -v
		docker-compose up --build

step 6: psql -h localhost -p 5432 -U scdf_username -d scdf_db
		password:scdf_password

=====================================================================================

Set up GUI for PostgreSQL:
# pgAdmin 4
1. Download and install pgAdmin 4 from the official website.
2. Open pgAdmin 4 and create a new server connection with the following details:
  - Name: SCDF Server (anything you prefer)
    - Connection Tab:
  - Host: localhost
  - Port: 5432
  - Username: scdf_username
  - Password: scdf_password
  - Database: scdf_db

=====================================================================================

include 2 emulator::

npm install --save react-native-get-random-values

npx react-native start --reset-cache

